<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n10067a"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n10" href="#n10067a">N10 (VI.B.16)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n10all.htm#n10067a"> 67(a)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> <font face="wake">X</font> alone excepted</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">&hellip; les cartes destin&eacute;es &agrave; circuler dans les pays de l&apos;Union postale portent la mention &eacute;crite en fran&ccedil;ais: / CARTE POSTALE.&mdash;UNION POSTALE UNIVERSALE <font color="green">[&hellip;]</font> Cette mention se trouve <i>inscrite en fran&ccedil;ais sur toutes les cartes postales de tous les Etats de l&apos;Union</i>, y compris l&apos;Allemagne, comme le montre la figure 101; seule, l&apos;Administration des Postes de la R&eacute;publique fran&ccedil;aise, qui ne poss&egrave;de qu&apos;<mark>un seul type</mark> de carte postale, &agrave; 10 centimes, pouvant circuler dans toute l&apos;<i>Union postale universelle</i>, <mark>ne porte pas cette mention</mark>. <font color="green">[&hellip; cards destined to circulate in Postal Union countries bear the endorsement, written in French: POST CARD.&mdash;UNIVERSAL POSTAL UNION [&hellip;]</font> This notice may be found written in French on every postcard in all Union States, including Germany, as figure 101 shows. The Postal Adminstration of the French Republic, which has only a single type of postcard, at 10 centimes, which can circulate through the whole Postal Union, is unique in not carrying this inscription.] <small> Eug&egrave;ne Gallois, <a name="EGLP" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#EGLP"><cite title="source">La Poste</cite></a> (1894) 292-4</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
